## Smells Scanned — No Findings (Clean)

The remaining 15 smells from the catalog were checked and found **clean**:

| Smell | Status | Notes |
|-------|--------|-------|
| Mystery Guest | ✅ Clean | Uses in-memory SQLite — no external files/services |
| Eager Test | ✅ Clean | No method calls 4+ distinct production methods; multi-call patterns are appropriate for integration scope |
| Magic Number Test | ✅ Clean | `3` and `10` in count assertions are self-documenting (items just inserted) |
| Sensitive Equality | ✅ Clean | No `.ToString()` in assertions |
| Exception Handling | ✅ Clean | No `try`/`catch` in test methods |
| General Fixture | ✅ Clean | `_connection` and `_repository` used by all 8 tests |
| Ignored/Disabled Test | ✅ Clean | No `[Ignore]` attributes |
| Duplicate Assert | ✅ Clean | No duplicate assertion statements |
| Lazy Test | ✅ Clean | Tests share repository methods but verify distinct behaviors |
| Constructor Initialization | ✅ Clean | Uses `[TestInitialize]` correctly |
| Default Test | ✅ Clean | Class properly named |
| Redundant Print | ✅ Clean | No `Console.Write`/debug output |
| Redundant Assertion | ✅ Clean | No tautological assertions |
| Resource Optimism | ✅ Clean | In-memory DB, no file-system assumptions |
| Empty Test | ✅ Clean | All methods have executable code |

## Well-Written Tests Worth Highlighting

- **`DeleteUser_RemovesFromDatabase`** — Clean arrange/act/assert, single clear behavior, explicit null-check assertion.
- **`InsertUser_ConcurrentInserts_MaintainsIntegrity`** — Tests a real concurrency scenario with a concrete count assertion. Good integration test design.
- **`ListUsers_ReturnsAllInserted`** — Uses `CollectionAssert.AllItemsAreNotNull` alongside count — good use of MSTest's collection assertions.

---

## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Fix | Effort | Impact |
|----------|-------|-----|--------|--------|
| **1** | Assertion-Free Test | Add count assertion to `BulkInsert` | ~2 min | Eliminates false-pass risk |
| **2** | Conditional Test Logic | Split `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` into 2 tests | ~5 min | Removes dead test path |
